Package: fddml
Title: Fuzzy Difference-in-Differences with Machine Learning
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Andres", "Mena", email = "andres_mena@brown.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = ""))
  )
Description: Doubly robust GMM estimators for fuzzy difference-in-differences
    designs with high-dimensional covariates. Implements the DML-Wald and
    DML-TC estimators of Mena (2026) with cross-fitted nuisance estimation
    via Lasso, Random Forest, neural networks, or OLS. Includes optimal
    propensity score trimming, clustered standard errors, and a bundled
    empirical application to the INPRES school construction program.
